content:
Transfer Files During a Chat

Give customers the ability to upload and transfer files during a chat so they can easily share more information about their issues.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Performance Editions, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud.

To use this feature:

Chat is enabled and set up
Chat is set up in a Salesforce console app

User permissions needed: Edit on the object

The legacy chat product will be retired on February 14, 2026. You should migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

For example, a customer can upload and transfer a screenshot of an error message to the agent.

The file size canâ€™t exceed 5 MB. Click the file transfer icon to initiate the file transfer. Select the record to attach the transferred file to. The customer receives a prompt to upload their file to the chat window. When sent, click the link in the chat log to view the file.
title: Transferring Files During Chat Sessions
